               <history>
                  <origin>Completed by an unidentified scribe for a <q>Mister Rocheby</q>, probably
                     in the <origPlace cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                        key="place_7000208">Indian subcontinent</origPlace>
                     <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1813-08">Sha‘bān 1228 (Aug 1813
                        CE)</origDate>.</origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Subsequently acquired by an unidentified individual who signed his named
                           <q>W. L. Mor...</q> with the remainder of the flyleaf regrettably torn
                        off. While the circumstances under which this volume arrived in <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7008653" cert="high"
                           >Britain</placeName> remain unclear, <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781" key="place_7011781"
                           >London</placeName> bookseller <persName role="bsl"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5679225/" key="person_5679225">Bernard Quaritch
                           (1819–1899)</persName> offered it for sale in his <date>30 Nov
                           1870</date> catalogue, p. 237, no 970, as part of the library of
                        Lieutenant Governor of the Northwest Provinces, <persName>John Russell
                           Colvin (1807–1857)</persName>. However, whether Colvin, in fact owned
                        this manuscript remains unclear, as Quaritch may have added it to that
                        catalogue for expeidiencey. Nevertheless, it seems that <persName
                           role="fmo ins" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058"
                           >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford (1812–1880)</persName> then
                        acquired it, probably for the advertised price of £3 16 shillings, and
                        accessioned it into his <orgName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/295427552"
                           key="person_295427552">Bibliotheca Lindesiana</orgName> at Haigh Hall,
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010384"
                           key="place_7010384">Wigan</placeName>. </p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379"
                           change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/" key="person_9985420">James Ludovic
                           Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName key="person_f6379" change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta
                           Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1908"
                           >1908</date> to the <orgName type="corporation" role="rps"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/">John Rylands Library</orgName>,
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010477"
                           key="place_7010477">Manchester</placeName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
